      <h1>Get Equipment & Parts</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Source the necessary components for your FTC robot.</p>
      <section class="content-section">
        <p>Start with the official FTC kit and a small set of reliable tools before buying extra hardware. A lean parts list keeps the team focused and avoids spending money on items you will not use.</p>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Useful starter items</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Robot kit or approved chassis components</li>
            <li>Hex keys, screwdrivers, wire cutters, and zip ties</li>
            <li>Batteries, chargers, and labeled storage bins</li>
            <li>Extra screws, gears, wheels, and other wear parts</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Action:</strong> Build a shared inventory so the team knows what it already has before ordering anything new.</p>
